(39, 6, 'Yaqzan Almagribi', 'yaqzanal25@gmail.com', '085156432716', 'uploads/cv\\fdcb5976-441b-4d3c-8eeb-80bfad7fee96.pdf', 'YAQZAN ALMAGRIBI\nBekasi, Jawa Barat | +6287846645106 | yaqzanal25@gmail.com\nlinkedin.com/in/yaqzanalmagribi\nI am a mechatronics engineer with expertise in mechanics, electronics, and\ninformatics. I have 8 months of professional experience working at PT Toyota Motor\nManufacturing Indonesia. During my time in university, I was actively involved in\nvarious organizational activities, committees, and competitions in the fields of\nProgrammable Logic Controllers (PLC) and the Internet of Things (IoT). My main\ninterests in the development of industrial automation technologies, robotics, and\nproduction processes. I am strongly committed to continuous learning, improving my\nskills, and applying my knowledge to contribute the advancement industrial sector.\nSKIILS & COMPETENCY\nPLC Programming Electrical Wiring SCADA Process Engineer\nMicrocontroller 3D Part Designer Python Project Engineer\nInternet of Things Mechanical Microsoft Office Production Engineer\nEDUCATION\nPoliteknik Astra 2022 - 2025\nDiploma-3 , Mechatronics GPA : 3.93/4.00\nTop GPA and Outstanding Student of the Mechatronics Engineering Program.\nFull Scholarship from Astra.\nSMK Telekomunikasi Telesandi Bekasi 2019 - 2022\nTeknik Telekomunikasi\nRanked 1st in major with an Average Score of 89.01\nTop 5 Finalist in the Technology Innovation Competition by Balitbangda, Bekasi Regency, with a\nproject on Automatic Body Temperature Scanner and Face Mask Detection System.\nWORK EXPERIENCE\nPT. TOYOTA MOTOR MANUFACTURING INDONESIA Feb 2025 - July 2025\nAssy & Painting Production Division - Assy & Painting Engineering Service Dept.\nResponsible for designing, developing, and ensuring the continuity of production processes in the\nassembly and painting lines included technical planning, process improvement and quality control.\nEngine Production Sunter Division - Maintenance Dept. Dec 2024 - Feb 2025\nResponsible for effective implementation of the three key pillars of maintenance: preventive, predictive,\nand corrective actions. Problem analysis on issues production line and develop machine conectivity.\nPUSAT PENELITIAN TEKNOLOGI DAN KOMUNIKASI ITB Jan 2021 - March 2021\nProgrammer and Electrical Microcontroller IoT\nSuccessfully developed the Automatic Attendance System using RFID, Automatic Smoke Detector, and\nAutomatic Soil Moisture Monitoring System, for students at SMK Telekomunikasi Telesandi Bekasi.\nPROJECT EXPERIENCE\nAutomatic Supply Material PT-ED Painting Line March 2025 - July 2025\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully develop, designed, planned, and collaborated with the production and maintenance teams\nto reduce manpower working time and collect actual material data.\nQan Level Up Pokayoke No Clip Roof Outflow in Siller Painting Line May 2025 - July 2025\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully designed and planned a solution based on Pareto problem analysis issues in the Blackout\nArea of the Painting Line by developing an AI-based Pokayoke system.\nSwitch Dimmer Pokayoke Based On E-Harigami Trimming 2 Assy Line Feb 2025 - May 2025\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully developed, designed, and programmed a solution to address frequent part installation\nerrors at the switch dimmer trimming post in Assembly Line 2. Collaborated closely with the production\nteam to achieve one voice in problem-solving and implementation.\nQan Level Up Pokayoke No Spray Outflow in Black Out Painting Line May 2025 - July 2025\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully designed and planned a solution based on Pareto problem analysis issues in the Siller Area.\nMesh Wi-fi IoT Integrated Machine Connectivity December 2024\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully implemented a 5G Mesh Wi-Fi system on the machining production line of Engine TR Plant 1.\nPortable Machine Connectivity IoT Device January 2024\nPT. Toyota Motor Manufacturing Indonesia\nSuccessfully collected temperature parameter data from machines on the Engine TR production line.\nNavigation, Controller and Electrical Autonomous AGV Sept 2024 - Nov 2024\nPT. United Tractors Pandu Engineering\nSuccessfully developed the AGV controller wiring system, programmed the STM32 microcontroller,\nand implemented the navigation system using ROS2 for an autonomous AGV.\nElectrical Simulator Car August 2024 - Sept 2024\nPT. Maxxima Innovative Engineering\nSuccessfully carried out the installation of electrical simulator systems on 3 units of Corolla Altis, 3\nunits of Pajero Sport, and 3 units of Hino Dutro vehicles.\nSmart Aquaponik Internet of Things System July 2024\nPoliteknik Astra\nSuccessfully handled programming for the microcontroller and developed the application using Android\nStudio, as well as installed and integrated the electrical components and sensors used in the system.\nKontes Robot Tematik Indonesia (KRTMI) March 2024 - July 2024\nPusat Prestasi Nasional Kemendikbud\nSuccessfully led the team in concept planning, component selection, and robot system design, while\nbeing technically responsible for the programming, electrical, and mechanical divisions.\nORGANIZATIONAL AND COMMITTEE EXPERIENCE\nHead of Department, Academic Potential Development for Mechatronics Student Feb 2024 - Feb 2025\nPoliteknik Astra\nSuccessfully managed the department responsible for planning and developing the Academic Program\nfor Mechatronics Students at Astra Polytechnic.\nVice Chair, Student Robotics Organization March 2023 - Feb 2024\nPoliteknik Astra\nSuccessfully carried out responsibilities by organizing Robotics Student Activity Unit programs, including\nProject-Based Learning, research, and robotics education activities.\nChief Organizer, Mechatronics of Astra Polytechnic Festival - National PLC Competition Sept 2024\nPoliteknik Astra\nSuccessfully organized a national-level event for high school, vocational school, and university students,\ntargeting 100 participants from across the country.\nACHIEVEMENTS\nAstra Polytechnic Scholarship - PT Astra Bina Ilmu Foundation 2022 - 2025\nScholarship recipient at Astra Polytechnic awarded by PT Astra Bina Ilmu Foundation, with full tuition coverage.\nFinalist Kontes Robot Tematik Indonesia 2024\nTeam Leader of the finalist team in the Indonesian Thematic Robot Contest by Pusat Prestasi Nasional.\n3rd Winner Competitor National PLC Competition 2024\n3rd Place Winner - National PLC Competition, Universitas Muhammadiyah Tangerang by OMRON.\nFinalist Top 5 Fuse National PLC Competition 2024\nTop 5 Finalist - National PLC Competition, Politeknik Manufaktur Bandung by OMRON.\n1st Winner Novastech Program Kreativitas Mahasiswa 2023\n1st Place Winner - Novastech, Student Creativity Program (PKM), organized by Astra Polytechnic.\nSOFT SKILLS\nLanguage: English (Intermediate), Indonesia (Native)\nLeadership Project | Strong Communication Skills | Responsible and Reliable | Adaptable and\nQuick to Learn | Public Speaking | Time Management | Teamwork and Collaboration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2026-05-01 01:55:56'),
